stylometry: Goal seek is intended to be a what if scenario. Goal seek is almost like cause and effect. It changes a a certain variable that will then change a outcome result. For example, lets see there is a levy is trying to be passed. The levy require 2/3 votes in order to be passed.  The results are in and if the levy required 2/3 yes votes, which would be 65 percent, and only got 55 percent of the votes to be yes and 45 percent votes to be no, we then can ask a few questions and using goal seek answer these questions. We can ask how many "no" votes are needed to be converted into "yes" votes in order for the levy to be passed. Using goal seek we can solve for this problem. Data table looks at a range of possible outcomes. Data table can only use one or two variables. But it allows us at a quick glance to see possible end results to given criteria. For example we can use a data table to maximize profits for a company. We can find at what percent of products sold would generate a profit for a particular company.
